                            <comment id="88585" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2014 14:23:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch has been landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86764" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 17 Jun 2014 00:29:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10733/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10733/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86503" author="yong.fan" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 23:50:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas, I prefer to land the patch to 2.6, because orphan is introduced by the LFSCK for MDT-OST inconsistency in 2.6. If we do not fix that in time, the namespace LFSCK on orphan may regard the orphan as update case. Although it is not fatal issue and can be handled, it is still some confused. In fact, I have made the patch already. But I will not push it to gerrit until the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10579/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10579/&lt;/a&gt; has been landed firstly, then avoid unnecessary refreshing the existing patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86436" author="adilger" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 17:11:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fan Yong, do you think this is critical for 2.6 or could it be fixed in 2.7?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
